HEADWORD: Burgage
<hw>Burg"age</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Burg</er>: cf. F. <ets>bourgage</ets>, LL.
<ets>burgagium</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Eng. Law)</fld> <def>A tenure by
which houses or lands are held of the king or other lord of a borough or
city; at a certain yearly rent, or by services relating to trade or
handicraft.</def> <rj><au>Burrill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

